-- Wells Fargo CFO Sloan Calls Pace of Recovery ‘Frustrating’
-- B y   L a u r a   M a r c i n e k
-- 2012-05-01T12:17:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-01/wells-fargo-cfo-sloan-calls-pace-of-recovery-frustrating-.html
Wells Fargo & Co. (WFC)  Chief Financial
Officer Tim Sloan said the pace of the economic recovery has
been “frustrating.”  The bank had expected the rebound from the recession would
be stronger, Sloan said today at an investor presentation. Wells
Fargo, the largest bank on the U.S. West Coast, is based in San
Francisco.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laura Marcinek in New York at 
